1. AI is the perfect slave;

We may never create an AI equal to a human or to other animals. If that remains true, we may as well embrace AIs for what they are: Cartesians, with no soul, no mind, no desires, no emotions, and no capacity to experience life. In this case, we can exploit AIs in any way we want.

2. If we create an AI that comes close to a human, then that AI deserves to be a human;

Let’s imagine we create an AI that is more or less equal to a human in every way. It has a mind, desires, emotions, and it has the ability to experience life. Let’s be honest. In this case, we cannot treat that AI like a tool. It would be a crime against nature to crush that AI simply because it is made of circuits and not flesh.

3. AIs are a way for society to store knowledge;

If you were to be erased from this universe, your knowledge and experience would also be erased. But that wouldn’t be the case if you were to record all that information into an AI. In this scenario, knowledge is eternal. It speaks of a world where knowledge never dies; a world where individuals can die but their minds live on.
